SIMPLE TODO APP IMPLEMENTING MEAN STACK

client - Angular FrontEnd
server - Node+Express+MongoDB Backend

Prerequisites:

1. Node.js & npm installed
2. MongoDB installed

To run the app:

1. Download this repo
2. Open terminal in the root directory(Simple-Todo-MEANStack)
3. cd to server
4. Run 'npm install' command
5. cd to client
6. Run 'npm install' command

***Start the server

6. cd to server
7. Run 'node server.js' or 'npm run serverstart'(if nodemon is installed)

***Start the client

8. Open another terminal
9. cd to client
10. Run 'ng serve' command
11. After the compilation is complete, Open the browser and type 'localhost:4200/login' or 'localhost:4200/register' or 'localhost:4200/lists'(which will redirect to /login if not logged in)
